{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"54e46800-e2d4-4d13-99ff-24fecf2edcbc","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n**`.csproj` — 2 changes:**\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the unified `MSTest` v3 package (it bundles the test framework, adapter, and SDK)\n\n**Test code** — no changes needed. The namespace and attributes are the same.\n\nWant me to apply these changes?\n\n<details>\n<summary>Proposed .csproj</summary>\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net462</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.2\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n</details>","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8fa5213a-cef9-4e5e-8729-509a662e64ec","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n\n1. A .csproj targeting `net462` with an assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. A `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference (old version 17.5.0)\n3. Test code using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` package (v3.x) which is the unified meta-package for MSTest v3 (replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`)\n\n\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a recent version\n4. **Update** the target framework if needed — MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+ and .NET 6+, though moving to .NET 6 or later is the recommended path forward\n\n.\n\nThe migration path involves removing the assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` and replacing it with the unified `MSTest` NuGet package (v3.x), which bundles everything together. The namespace remains